            "en-x-generated": "<p>The conditions for getting married are determined by the law of the country of one's nationality. The main marriage conditions for Belgians are: minimum age: the minimum age for marriage is 18. The youth court can lift this age restriction if there are good reasons to do so. consent of the spouses: both partners must voluntarily consent to the marriage. A forced marriage is therefore prohibited. absence of an impediment to marriage: marriages between persons who are too close by blood or affinity are prohibited. The king may, for important reasons, lift that prohibition. Such a request must be addressed to the Minister of Justice. ban on bigamy: a person who is already married may not enter into another marriage. This prohibition also applies to foreigners marrying in Belgium, even if their own national law allows polygamy. Bigamy is a criminal offence. prohibition of marriage of convenience: a marriage in which the intention of at least one of the spouses is not to establish a lasting community of life but only to obtain a residence benefit is prohibited. The conditions for foreigners are determined by their own national law.</p>"
